{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-00404/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-00404"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:04:04"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["high"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tracking, tilt"]}},{"label":{"none":["Lighting"]},"value":{"none":["low key"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A label reading \"Woodcock London\" is sewn by hand into a jacket."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00404/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-00404","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00404/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-00404"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00404/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00404/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00404/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00404/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00404/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00404/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00404/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00404/canvas/1/0b8aeb84-4a39-4187-a924-822226d77c67","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T15:17:13.190Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The camera movement culminates in the painstaking sewing of the garment’s label, which highlights that this is a product of the House of Woodcock. Everything under this room must be careful, deliberate, and secure, just like the labeling of the garment that shares Reynolds’ qualities.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00404/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:239.53947368421052,290.9429824561404,236.6228070175439,198.7390350877193"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00404/canvas/1/50121f90-e169-4681-ac89-c3c71c965fff","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T15:17:38.950Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>While writing, PTA’s placeholder name for Reynolds was “Arthur Dapple, Jr.” (Buchanan, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW50811787 BCX0\" href=\"https://www.vulture.com/2017/12/director-paul-thomas-anderson-on-phantom-thread-mortality.html\"><u>Love, Death, and Control</u></a>”). Daniel Day-Lewis ultimately came up with the name “Reynolds Woodcock,” a moniker that brought both the actor and director to tears. It’s a name that aligns well with many of PTA’s other creations (for example, Dirk Diggler or Daniel Plainview) in how it foregrounds the character’s sexuality to an almost ridiculous degree and speaks to their personality. It’s at once stuffy and silly.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00404/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:541.7763157894736,274.72587719298247,591.0416666666665,241.98464912280696"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00404/canvas/1/90eaee9e-6765-4bba-a4b1-be6ff95d9068","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T15:18:00.311Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>While <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW210373208 BCX0\" href=\"https://ptannotated.com/items/phan-04015.html\"><u>Alma’s name</u></a> will be sewn into the lining of the dress, kept secret, Reynolds’s name—Woodcock—is sewn on the outside, making his identity a part of the clothing. While Alma’s name is erased, subsumed into his creation, he ensures that he will be recognized for his clothing. The choice to make his last name the name of his company shows how closely he has tied his selfhood to his craft.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00404/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:612.6315789473684,550.9758771929824,719.7807017543859,313.14692982456154"}}}]}]}]}